    Coming at it from another direction, I'm not happy about this post.<p>As a developer looking at job posts, this was a quick keyword I could filter for jobs I /did not want/. The more times it gets brought up as a red flag that <br />"rockstar jobs" aren't "good jobs", the less often people will call them that. Hence, the likelier it is that bad jobs will go unlabeled. A useful negative buzzword is helpful, sometimes. Think of tells in poker.</p>

    
    
    
    
    
